<document>
  <properties>
    <author email="mcconnell@dpml.net">Stephen McConnell</author>
    <title>DPML Transit</title>
  </properties> 

  <body>
    <section name="Runtime Deployment Model">

        <p>Using information derived from system properties and command line options, the 
           Transit Application Launcher will build up a map containing keys and options
           to be supplied as an optional constructor argument.</p>

        <p>Constructor argument values populated by the launcher and supplied to
           the transit repository plugin handler are detailed in the following table.</p>

        <table>
          <tr>
            <th>Argument</th>
            <th>Description</th>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Map</td>
            <td>
             Will be supplied with the Transit context map.
            </td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>String[]</td>
            <td>
             Will be supplied with the remaining command line arguments following
             removal of standard and -X cli options recognized by Transit.
            </td>
          </tr>
        </table>

        <p>Transit context map keys and values are detailed in the following table.</p>

        <table>
          <tr>
            <th>Key</th>
            <th>Value</th>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>urn:transit.debug.policy</td>
            <td>
             A Boolean value declaring the debug policy.
            </td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>urn:transit.cli.args</td>
            <td>
             The non-processed cli arguments.
            </td>
          </tr>
        </table>

    </section>

  </body>

</document>

